         <acqinfo>
            <head>Acquisition Information</head>
            <p>This collection was given to the Library by Charles C.
            Abbott of Pomfret Center, Connecticut, through the Rare
            Book Division on five different occasions: #5368, November
            29, 1973; #5368-a, August 21, 1974; #5368-b, April 18,
            1980; #5368-c, April 18, 1980; and, #5368-d, August 13,
            1980.</p>
         </acqinfo>
      </descgrp>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>This collection consists of ca. 700 items, 16th to 20th
         centuries, primarily engravings, prints, drawings, magazine
         photographs, and modern reproductions depicting Oliver
         Cromwell. In addition, there are prints of Cromwell's
         contemporaries, battle scenes, and group pictures in which
         Cromwell appears, and town views and maps from Cromwell's
         periods. Several legal documents, 1642-1659; photocopies and
         transcript of manuscripts; newspaper clippings, 1841-1934; and
         an indexed scrapbook, 1837-1849, of newspaper clippings, all
         concerning Cromwell, are also present. A list of engravers of
         portraits of Cromwell and a plaster cast of a death mask of
         Cromwell complete the collection.</p>
      </scopecontent>
